- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the analysis of social media platforms and their use during crisis situations. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of social bots on society and communication during crisis situations. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may involve the development of tools or methods for identifying and analysing social bots. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the security implications of social bots during crisis situations. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the interaction between humans and social bots during crisis situations.
